wers, and locker rooms shall not have cameras where children can be in a state of undress. (b) The recorded footage from the cameras shall be maintained for a full year. NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to require that all schools maintain cameras in areas where students are present in schools.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: